news.title: Check bylaw violations before ordering demolition: Karnataka HC to BBMP
news.para: Justice Suraj Govindaraj has made this observation while disposing of a batch of petitions filed by owners of sites formed in Remco (BHEL) Layout, Bengaluru.

news.title: Gujarat RERA to buy Rs 44 crore Guda plot for its HQ near Sargasan
news.para: The authority is likely to buy a plot of around 3,500 sq metres from the Gandhinagar Urban Development Authority (Guda) for around Rs 44 crore. The procedure to buy the land will soon begin.

news.title: Big plots unsold, Ahmedabad civic body to put 150 smaller ones on the block
news.para: The AMC saw very limited interest in its Feb 2023 auction, where seven plots with a cumulative base price of Rs 499.72 crore were up for grabs.

news.title: Seven builders in Noida agree to pay 25% dues as part of new policy to revive stuck projects
news.para: This is part of a one-time settlement scheme to revive stalled real estate projects. This follows the authority’s approval of the recommendations of a committee chaired by former NITI Aayog chairman and G20 Sherpa Amitabh Kant.

news.title: Union Living to invest Rs 10 crore to set up new centres in Mumbai
news.para: Union living was started by two co-founders in 2020. Currently, it has 1,050 operational beds across nine properties in Mumbai, Pune and Ahmedabad.

news.title: Ghaziabad: NGT directs Nipun Builders & Developers not to continue with its group housing project
news.para: ​The tribunal was hearing a petition claiming that the realtor, Nipun Builders and Developers Pvt Ltd., in Ghaziabad was continuing with its group housing project 'Nipun Saffron Valley' in violation of environmental norms.

news.title: Jamshyd Godrej resigns as non-executive director of Godrej Properties
news.para: In a regulatory filing, Godrej Properties informed that "Jamshyd Godrej, Non- Executive Non-Independent Director of the company has tendered his resignation from directorship of the company, having attained the age of 75 years, with effect from January 24, 2024".

news.title: Havells India's net profit up 1.55% in Q3 FY24
news.para: Havells India's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 4,469.75 crore, a growth of 7.26 per cent from Rs 4,167.21 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Pune: PMRDA keeps 20 building plans on hold over access to water
news.para: These projects are located in the Maval, Mulshi and Haveli talukas of Pune district where construction activities are booming.

news.title: Puravankara posts net profit of Rs 77.79 crore in Q3 FY24
news.para: Puravankara's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 595.88 crore, a growth of 45.19 per cent from Rs 410.40 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: SMFG Grihashakti raises Rs 300 crore long-tenor funds from National Housing Bank
news.para: As on December 31, 2023, SMFG Grihashakti's assets under management (AUM) stands at Rs 8,028 crore, showing a 37% CAGR growth over last two years.

news.title: Bigbloc Construction's net profit up 12.11% in Q3 FY24
news.para: Bigbloc Construction's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 61.52 crore, a growth of 24.18 per cent from Rs 49.54 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Hi-Tech Pipes aims 10 lakh tonne production capacity by FY25
news.para: Hi-Tech Pipes also announced commissioning of its Sanand unit-II Phase-1 at Gujarat and establishment of new greenfield unit-III at Sikandrabad (UP) and Sanand Unit-II Phase-2.

news.title: Gmada yet to pay relief for land acquired in Mohali sector 101
news.para: They have now threatened that if the authority does not take any concrete action in this regard till January 31, then they would stage a major protest outside the Gmada Bhawan.

news.title: Nashik: Allotment of smaller plots by MIDC soon
news.para: An MIDC official, while talking to TOI, said two highly reputed firms, including a state-owned oil marketing company, have decided to invest Rs 2,500 crore for setting up a pharma company and manufacturing cryogenic tanks at the new industrial estate.

news.title: Kolte-Patil acquires two society re-development projects in Mumbai
news.para: The two acquired projects are located at Dahisar and Versova. With these additions, Kolte-Patil Developers now has of a total of fifteen projects in the Mumbai Metropolitan Region (MMR).

news.title: Gurugram civic body directs officials to complete checks on property tax data in two days
news.para: For this, the corporation will rope in market associations, residents welfare associations (RWAs) and residents to set up camps to complete the process.

news.title: Gujarat: NA certification process likely to be removed from areas with town planning schemes
news.para: After receiving the feedback that the NA certification process was extremely cumbersome and must be reformed, the committee submitted its recommendations to the government.

news.title: Eighteen months after SC order, demolition drive in Faridabad Aravalis kicks off
news.para: The department has identified 600 such illegal structures in Ankhir and Mewal Maharajpur villages of the district. Land in these villages falls under Section 4 (special orders) of the Punjab Land Preservation Act (PLPA), which deems an area as forest land under the Forest (Conservation) Act, 1980.

news.title: Hyderabad: Fate of 30,000 two-BHKs in limbo as GHMC awaits Rs 1,500 crore to finish pending work
news.para: As these 2-BHK houses were launched in the previous government’s tenure, the GHMC is in a dilemma over taking up construction works for 30,000 plus units until the new government sanctions the budget to resume the activity.
